paragraphs:
[26]
Subsection 3(3) of the
IRPA
states:
"
Application
"3(3) This Act is to be constructed and applied in a manner that
(a) furthers the domestic and international interests of Canada;
(b) promotes accountability and transparency by enhancing public awareness of immigration and refugee programs;
(c) facilitates cooperation between the Government of Canada, provincial governments, foreign states, international organizations and non-governmental organizations;
(d) ensures that decisions taken under this Act are consistent with the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms, including its principles of equality and freedom from discrimination and of the equality of English and French as the official languages ​​of Canada;
(e) supports the commitment of the Government of Canada to enhance the vitality of the English and French linguistic minority communities in Canada; and
(f) complies with international human rights instruments to which Canada is signatory."
"
Interpretation and implementation
"3(3) The interpretation and implementation of this Act shall have the effect of:
(a) to promote the interests of Canada domestically and internationally;
b) encourage accountability and transparency through better knowledge of immigration and refugee programs;
(c) to facilitate cooperation between the federal government, provincial governments, foreign states, international organizations and non-governmental organizations;
(d) to ensure that decisions taken under this Act are consistent with the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms, particularly with regard to the principles, on the one hand, of equality and protection against discrimination and, on the other hand, of the equality of French and English as official languages of Canada;
e) to support the Government of Canada's commitment to promoting the development of Canada's French-speaking and English-speaking minorities;
f) to comply with international human rights instruments to which Canada is a signatory."
